<LabLayout title="Lab 16 · Clock tree → baud rate (break it, then fix it) — Firmware Labs">
  <LabShell
    num="LAB 16"
    title="Clock tree → baud rate (break it, then fix it)"
    tag="Hub S1 reinforcement"
    why='<b>Where this bites you:</b> you already studied clocks — this makes it muscle memory. Configure the tree, then press "change clocks, forget BRR" and watch the UART silently break. That exact bug is a favorite interview scenario.'
    takeaway='<b>The answer pattern:</b> "Baud is derived from the peripheral clock through BRR. Changing SYSCLK or a bus divider changes f_periph but BRR keeps its old value → actual baud diverges → framing errors / garbage. Fix: recalculate BRR after <i>any</i> clock change, and check which APB bus the UART hangs off in the clock tree." UART tolerates roughly ±2% baud error.'
  >
    <ClockTree />
  </LabShell>
</LabLayout>
